00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:40,000
And I don't want to say anything about different corporations.

393
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:46,000
So I won't name the corporation, but he had a glass ceiling also, which, you know,

394
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:52,000
did you talk as you were raising your own children?

395
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Did you talk to them at the experiences that you would have?

396
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:58,000
I did not.

397
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,000
No.

398
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:05,000
You know, my mother didn't tell me, well, she would show me these history books.

399
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:08,000
And I would see and read in the history books.

400
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:14,000
But she didn't want to prejudice me against people, which I can appreciate.

401
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,000
And I didn't want to do that to my children either.

402
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:23,000
I know I took them out of school, uh, an ice date home that day and took on Martin Luther King's birthday.

403
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:26,000
I would take them to the museum, you know.

404
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:30,000
That was the big black thing that we did, I guess.

405
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:34,000
Before it was a national holiday, you know.

406
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Right.

407
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:40,000
What about getting positive, which is a black people in schools?

408
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:44,000
It's like that wasn't happening for your children?

